main event: A visual observation of a white blob object occurred on July 6, 1954, in Manston, England.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for 6-8 seconds., The object appeared to be moving upwards at a very high speed., The observer was considered a reliable source with considerable flying experience., The local meteorological station found no unusual weather phenomena at the time., The report concluded there was insufficient data for analysis.
witness description: The observer is a navigator with considerable flying experience.
